<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">
Abdomen with five ventrites in males with tip of 6th ventrite visible (
<figureCitation box="[927,991,154,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
B) and five ventrites in females (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1402,154,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A). Abdominal postcoxal lines recurved roundly and incomplete, almost reaching posterior margin of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1410,189,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A, B). In males apical margin of ventrite 5 truncate (
<figureCitation box="[727,797,224,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
B); ventrite 6 emarginate medially; tergite VIII rounded. Apodeme of male sternum IX simple, thin, rod-like. Tergite X rounded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1025,1090,258,281]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
M). In females apical margin of ventrite 5 rounded (
<figureCitation box="[364,428,293,316]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A); sternite VIII rounded, entire, with membranous part in middle appearing divided into two parts (
<figureCitation box="[217,281,328,351]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C), tergite VIII rounded. Proctiger (TX) membranous at base, elongate, rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1303,328,351]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
L).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">
Male terminalia and genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[524,598,362,385]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
H–J). Penis guide symmetrical, thin, with sides almost parallel, spindle shaped, widest at basal part in lateral view, with pointed apex; shorter than parameres. Parameres well developed, simple, setose apically. Penis base with capsule reduced. Penis simple, rod-like.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[401,481,466,489]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,192,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1437,191,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mada hirsuta sp. nov.; A) abdomen, female; B) abdomen, male; C) sternite VIII, female; D) antenna; E) mandible; F) labrum; G) proleg; H) tegmen, lateral; I) tegmen, ventral; J) penis, lateral; K) female genitalia, dorsal; L) female genitalia, ventral; M) male genital segment, dorsal; N) tarsal claw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264100/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
K, L). Coxites elongate, narrow at base, broadly widened at posterior part, styli not observed. Bursa copulatrix ending with oviduct, sperm duct diverges slightly below oviduct; sperm duct short, lightly sclerotized, simple; spermatheca small, membranous, vermiform, without clear nodulus and ramus; accessory gland thin, a bit longer than spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
